\par }{\cs27\b\f1\ul\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 2 Corinthians 3:12-}{\cs27\b\f1\ul\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 14}{
\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085  }{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 Seeing then that we have such hope, we use great plainness of speech: }{
\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 13}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  And not as Moses, which put a }
{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2191493\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 veil}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
 over his face, that the children of Israel could not stedfastly look to the end of that which is abolish\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 ed: }{\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 14}{
\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  But their minds were blinded: for until this day remaineth the same }{
\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2191493\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 veil}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
 untaken away in the reading of the old testament; which }{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2191493\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 veil}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085\charrsid13181473 
\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  is done away in Christ.}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid1391085 
\par }\pard\plain \s28\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10560229 \fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid1391085 
\par The Apostle\rquote s plain speech makes it very clear that the OT taught the same principles as the New, but not understood as such because \'93their minds were blinded\'94. With the coming of Christ, of whom we read yesterday: \'93}{\insrsid1391085 
are hid all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge}{\insrsid1391085 \'94 }{\cs25\f1\fs16\lang0\langfe1033\langnp0\insrsid1391085\charrsid1391085 (Col 2:3)}{\insrsid1391085 , the }{\insrsid2191493 veil}{\insrsid1391085  was lifted. 
\par 
\par One should rightly ask: if the message was the same from Old to New, how did the coming of Christ bring about more understanding? As always, the answer concerns morality. The God-man came to teach us
 and enable us to become moral. As a man becomes good, the \'93}{\insrsid2191493 veil}{\insrsid1391085 \'94 is progressively lifted from his eyes.
\par 
\par }{\cs27\b\f1\fs24\ul\insrsid3015488\charrsid3015488 2 Corithinans}{\cs27\b\f1\fs24\ul\insrsid10236559  }{\cs27\b\f1\fs24\ul\insrsid3015488\charrsid3015488 3:17-18}{\cs27\b\f1\fs24\ul\insrsid1391085\charrsid3015488  }{
\cs25\fs16\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af34\insrsid3015488\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 17}{\cs30\b\f1\fs24\insrsid3015488\charrsid13181473  Now the Lord is that Spirit: and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is liberty. }{
\cs25\fs16\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af34\insrsid3015488\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 18}{\cs30\b\f1\fs24\insrsid3015488\charrsid13181473  But we all, with open face beholding as in a glass the glory of the Lord, are changed into the same im
age from glory to glory, even as by the Spirit of the Lord}{\insrsid10044948\charrsid10560229 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2974322 \fs24\lang1033\langfe255\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af34\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp255 {\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid5855982 
\par }{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 This liberty which the Apostle speaks of was promised by the Son}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827 : }{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid12517813 If the Son therefore shall make you free, ye shall be free indeed!}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827  }{
\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid12517813 (John 8:36)}{\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  }{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827  Just before }{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827 this}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 
, our Lord told us that \'93}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 Whosoever committeth sin is the servant of sin}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 \'94 }{
\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 (John 8:34).}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827  The word servant may also be rendered \'93
slave\'94 (it is the Greek word }{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af182\hich\af182\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827 \'e4\'ef\'f5\'eb\'ef\'f2}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827  }{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid328827 ,}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid12517813\charrsid328827  \'93doulos\'94).
 The Spirit of the Lord, when He dwells in a man, brings about liberty, that is, the freedom to choose morally and correctly.  
\par }{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid328827 
\par This promise is the core of the \'93Good News\'94. Through Christ, and with much labor, we will become able to be truly, in every way free. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid328827 {\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid328827 However, this freedom does not come all at once. The Apostle also said: \'93}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid328827 For now we see through a glass, darkly; but then face to face: now I know in part; but then shall I know even as also I am known.}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827\charrsid328827 \'93}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827  }{\fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af43\hich\af43\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid328827  }{
