\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559  }{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
And it came to pass on the second sabbath after the first, that he went through the corn fields; and his disciples plucked the ears of corn, and did eat, rubbing them in their hands. }{
\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 2}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
 And certain of the Pharisees said unto them, Why do ye that which is not lawful to do on the sabbath days?
\par }{\cs26\f1\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 The day being described is Saturday, which was always a Sabbath day in the Jewish calendar. It is the \loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'93\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 second after the first\loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'94
\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 , because \loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'93\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 Sabbath\loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'94\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
 also means rest, and was a generic term for any Feast day. If a feast fell on a Friday, Saturday would \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 therefore\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 be the \loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'93
\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 second sabbath after the first\loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'94\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 . 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 The Pharisees were \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 complaining\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  because work\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  was forbidden on the Sabbath\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 , and they interpreted the 
\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 disciples\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 glea\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 n\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 ing of grain\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  as \loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'93
\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 work\loch\af1\dbch\af34\hich\f1 \'94\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 .
\par }{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid10236559 
\par }{\cs27\b\f1\ul\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 Luke 6:}{\cs27\b\f1\ul\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 3-4}{
\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149   }{\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 3}{
\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  And Jesus answering them said, Have ye not read so much as this, what David did, when himself was an hungred, and they which were with him; }{
\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid10560229 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 4}{\cs30\b\f1\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid13181473 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  How\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 
 he went into the house of God, and did take and eat the shewbread, and gave also to them that were with him; which it is not lawful to eat but for the priests alone? 
\par }{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2765149 {\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid2765149\charrsid2765149 The \'93shewbread\'94 was bread made of the finest flour, and placed o}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 n the holy table in the temple: 
\par }\pard \qj \li720\ri720\widctlpar\faauto\rin720\lin720\itap0\pararsid3309113 {\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 \'93}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 
And thou shalt take fine flour, and bake twelve cakes thereof: two tenth deals shall be in one cake.  }{\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 (6)}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113   And thou shalt set them in two rows, six on a row, upon the pure table before the LORD.}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 \'94 }{
\cs25\f1\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 (\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 Lev 24:5-6\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 )}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113  

\par 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3309113 {\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 This bread was renewed every Sabbath, and the old bread was eaten by the priests only. }{
