\par 
\par }\pard \qj \li720\ri720\widctlpar\faauto\rin720\lin720\itap0\pararsid3309113 {\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 \'93}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 
Now therefore what is under thine hand? give me five loaves of bread in mine hand, or what there is present.  }{\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 (4)}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113   And the priest answered David, and said, There is
 no common bread under mine hand, but there is hallowed bread; if the young men have kept themselves at least from women.  }{\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 (5)}{
\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113   And David answered the priest, and said unto him, Of a truth women have been kept from us about these three days, since I came o
ut, and the vessels of the young men are holy, and the bread is in a manner common, yea, though it were sanctified this day in the vessel.  }{\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 (6
)  }{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 So the priest gave him hallowed bread: for there was no bread there but the shewbread, that was taken from befo
re the LORD, to put hot bread in the day when it was taken away.}{\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113 \'94 }{\cs25\fs16\cf1\lang0\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af0\langnp0\langfenp1033\insrsid3309113\charrsid3309113 (
